{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-rendering/pullrequests/202/comments/124323374.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-rendering/pull-requests/202/_/diff#comment-124323374"}}, "parent": {"id": 124309883, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-rendering/pullrequests/202/comments/124309883.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-rendering/pull-requests/202/_/diff#comment-124309883"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 202, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-rendering/pullrequests/202.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-rendering/pull-requests/202"}}, "title": "Add ThermalCamera"}, "content": {"raw": "Regarding more uniform, do you mean same color throughout the object, i.e. flat shaded? The shaders output temperature and I convert them to gray scale in the [sample demo](#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-rendering/src/1801393715437fa7fcfdbd430a5117271ce9d313/examples/thermal_camera/GlutWindow.cc#lines-89). There are very slight variations in the temperature readings for each object \\(as a function of depth\\).", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Regarding more uniform, do you mean same color throughout the object, i.e. flat shaded? The shaders output temperature and I convert them to gray scale in the <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-rendering/src/1801393715437fa7fcfdbd430a5117271ce9d313/examples/thermal_camera/GlutWindow.cc#lines-89\" rel=\"nofollow\">sample demo</a>. There are very slight variations in the temperature readings for each object (as a function of depth).</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-11-11T21:45:54.102997+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Ian Chen", "uuid": "{eaa6fca5-6deb-43f6-907f-971c144735dd}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Beaa6fca5-6deb-43f6-907f-971c144735dd%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Beaa6fca5-